{"TopicId":175832,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"A mod for zooming in the VAB","CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T21:45:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-11T21:45:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince I am working on a cubesat mod of \u00A0a 20x20cm form factor, it would be really helpful if there were a mod that would allow us to zoom in as much as possible in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u00A0This would let smaller parts be used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T06:37:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E you hold shift and use the scroll wheel to zoom. In the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E it\u2019s just the scroll wheel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr do you mean zooming even closer than stock lets us?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T13:02:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck out WASD editor camera - that lets you move around feeely and has a fine movement key toggle as well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T13:51:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397822\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175832\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528785431\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr do you mean zooming even closer than stock lets us?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, exactly that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223397953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175832\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221528808569\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Drew Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Drew Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWASD editor camera\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLemme see!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-12T14:01:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse the \u0022HOLD SHIFT\u0022 trick to move your perspective as close as possible in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, sure, but not close enough? I highly recommend using the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E for technicals and\u00A0 tinys because you can move your perspective\u00A0\u003Cu\u003Ewherever you like\u003C/u\u003E. Hold SHIFT, right-click and drag to the desired view. One less mod to install and you can\u00A0just\u00A0jump to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E to launch it if you want, since version 1.4.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nP.S. You can get the perspective too close and even go straight through your craft!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-06-12T14:04:04Z\u0022 title=\u002206/12/2018 02:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJune 12, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Dark Lion\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Epostcript\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}